To  clarify what I mean when I say that I have the lowest and best prices
in North America, allow me to explain.  My prices are the lowest - that I
have  seen or heard of in this entire continent.  If anyone charges less,
I  am  not aware of them.  If you know of another dealer in North America
who  has  lower  prices  than  mine, please inform me and I will lower my
prices  permanently  for everyone.  Dealer  must have units available for
sale.   (Pretty  pointless to beat the price of a dealer who have nothing
to sell, right?)  And we are comparing FINAL DELIVERED prices, so be sure
to  include  the service charges for wiring money overseas if applicable,
sales tax, etc..  To get me to beat another dealer's price, the following
conditions must be met: (all very reasonable conditions)

  1. Dealer must have at least 10 units in inventory.
  2. Dealer must be based somewhere in North America.
  3. Dealer must provide warranty.
  4. Dealer  must  have  a  track  record of reliability.  Minimum 1 year
     experience  in  selling  and  servicing videogame cartridge copiers.
     No sense in beating the prices of a dealer that no one trusts.

Not  only  do  I  have  the lowest prices, I am never out-of-stock on any
item!!   You  pay;  you get.  Simple as that.  Ah, the benefits of living
practically right next door to the manufacturers of the copiers...

Videogame   cartridge   copiers   typically  go  through  many  revisions
throughout  their  lifetime.   American  and  Canadian  dealers  have  to
maintain  an  inventory  for  their  customers.  As a result, there is no
guarantee  that  you will receive the most recent version of the machine,
and  may  in  fact  be  buying  a months-old design fraught with bugs and
design  flaws.   Why subject yourself to all this grief?  The best way to
buy  a  videogame  cartridge  copier is through a Hong Kong-based dealer,
since  he/she  does  not  maintain  an  inventory and sells machines on a
per-order basis.  As a result, you are assured the most recent version of
the  machine.   I offer BIOS upgrades free-of-charge to all customers for
life,  to ensure that their purchases remain up-to-date for many years to
come.

Are  there  any problems getting the machine past US Customs?  US Customs
is  after bigger fish than a person who buys a single videogame cartridge
copier  and I have never EVER heard of a case where a customer who bought
a  single  videogame  cartridge  copier from overseas did not receive it.
All  orders are shipped to you clearly marked "Sample", thus facilitating
Customs  clearance.   In  the 3+ years that I was based in the US selling
videogame  cartridge  copiers,  I  typically  order 5 to 10 machines at a
time, and NEVER had a problem with US Customs.  Anyone who says otherwise
without proof is just using a scare tactic to prevent potential customers
from buying from a foreign dealer.

Customer service is a top priority with me!  Feel free to send email with
any  question you may have before-and-after the sale and you will receive
a  response  within 24 hours, usually much sooner.  I also maintain a ftp
site  where  you  can  find  many  documents  regarding  and  patches and
utilities  for videogame cartridge copiers (send email for information on
the ftp service).  No other dealer gives you so much, for so little.

The lowest prices...  Reliability...  Support...  How can you lose?

Oh, one last thing, shipping's on you...

The only way to get a copier for less is to buy a used one, steal one, or
ask  a  friend to buy one for you in Hong Kong.  Even with option 3, your
savings  are  minimal  and  you run the risk of picking up a refurblished
machine (ever hear of those "colored" MGH's?  Blue, green, etc..  <grin>)
which  are  primarily  sold  to unsuspecting tourists which almost always
break  down  within a matter of months.  Buying from me means buying with
experience  (3+  years  of  it).   I know what I am doing and will not be
duped  by  unscrupulous  dealers in Hong Kong (many of them).  I was born
there and spent my childhood there so I know my way around.

